<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<suppressions xmlns="https://jeremylong.github.io/DependencyCheck/dependency-suppression.1.3.xsd">

    <!--
      OWASP Dependency-Check suppressions.
      Every entry MUST include <notes> with:
        - Why this specific CVE does not apply to this project
        - Ticket/issue tracking the suppression for future review
        - Expiry date after which this suppression should be reconsidered

      DO NOT suppress CVEs that apply. Fix them instead.
    -->

    <!-- ─── Spring Boot Actuator: CVE-2026-22733 ───────────────────────
         Score: 8.2  Auth bypass via CloudFoundry Actuator path conflict.
         Full fix requires Spring Boot 4.0.4, but that is a major version
         jump. We are on 3.5.12 (latest 3.x patch). This CVE only applies
         when ALL of: (1) Spring Security in use, (2) an app endpoint path
         conflicts with the CloudFoundry actuator path (/cloudfoundryapplication/**),
         (3) CloudFoundry hosting is used.
         Our deployment is not on CloudFoundry. Management server port is
         isolated to internal network only (management.server.port=8081).
         Review: Ticket #blockchain-sec-001. Revisit when upgrading to SB 4.x. -->
    <suppress until="2026-12-31Z">
        <notes>CVE-2026-22733: CloudFoundry-specific auth bypass. Project is not
            deployed on CloudFoundry. Actuator port restricted to internal network.
            See ticket blockchain-sec-001. Revisit on Spring Boot 4.x upgrade.</notes>
        <cve>CVE-2026-22733</cve>
    </suppress>

    <!-- ─── Spring Context: CVE-2024-38820 / CVE-2025-22233 ───────────
         Score: 3.1  Locale-dependent DataBinder disallowedFields bypass.
         We do not use DataBinder.setDisallowedFields() anywhere in the
         codebase — we use constructor binding exclusively per the Spring
         recommendation. Grep confirms no disallowedFields usage.
         Review: blockchain-sec-002. Remove if disallowedFields is ever added. -->
    <suppress until="2026-06-30Z">
        <notes>CVE-2024-38820 / CVE-2025-22233: DataBinder.setDisallowedFields()
            locale bypass. Project uses constructor binding only; no disallowedFields
            calls exist in codebase (grep-verified). See blockchain-sec-002.</notes>
        <cve>CVE-2024-38820</cve>
        <cve>CVE-2025-22233</cve>
    </suppress>

    <!-- ─── XMLUnit: CVE-2024-31573 ───────────────────────────────────
         Score: 4.0  XSLT extension function RCE.
         XMLUnit is a test-scope dependency only (scope=test). It is never
         used at runtime. The attack requires processing untrusted XSLT
         stylesheets, which our tests do not do — we only compare fixed
         XML strings from known sources.
         Review: blockchain-sec-003. Upgrade to xmlunit 2.10.0+ when available
         in the test dependency chain. -->
    <suppress until="2026-06-30Z">
        <notes>CVE-2024-31573: XSLT extension RCE in XMLUnit. Test-scope only;
            never in production classpath. Tests use trusted XML only. Upgrade
            tracked in blockchain-sec-003.</notes>
        <cve>CVE-2024-31573</cve>
    </suppress>

    <!-- ─── AssertJ: CVE-2026-24400 ───────────────────────────────────
         Score: 7.3  XXE in XmlStringPrettyFormatter / isXmlEqualTo().
         assertj-core is test-scope only. We do not call isXmlEqualTo() or
         XmlStringPrettyFormatter.toXmlDocument() with untrusted XML in any
         test. All XML in our tests is internally generated.
         Action: Replace all isXmlEqualTo() calls with XMLUnit assertions per
         AssertJ's own deprecation guidance. Track in blockchain-sec-004.
         This suppression should be removed once blockchain-sec-004 is done. -->
    <suppress until="2026-03-31Z">
        <notes>CVE-2026-24400: XXE in AssertJ XmlStringPrettyFormatter.
            Test-scope only. No isXmlEqualTo() with untrusted input. Migration
            to XMLUnit in progress — see blockchain-sec-004. Remove this suppression
            when migration is complete.</notes>
        <cve>CVE-2026-24400</cve>
    </suppress>

    <!-- ─── Logback: CVE-2025-11226 / CVE-2024-12798 ──────────────────
         Score: 6.9 / 6.6  ACE via Janino + compromised logback config.
         These CVEs require: (1) Janino on classpath AND (2) write access to
         logback config OR control of an env variable pointing to a config.
         We do NOT have janino on the classpath (no spring-boot-starter-web
         dependency pulls it unless explicit). logback config is baked into the
         JAR at build time and not externally configurable.
         Note: Already upgraded to logback 1.5.25 which patches CVE-2024-12798.
         CVE-2025-11226 is also patched in 1.5.19+. This suppression is a
         belt-and-suspenders note that Janino is absent. -->
    <suppress until="2026-06-30Z">
        <notes>CVE-2025-11226 / CVE-2024-12798: ACE requires Janino on classpath.
            Janino is not a dependency of this project. Logback upgraded to 1.5.25
            which patches both CVEs. Suppression retained to document Janino absence.
            See blockchain-sec-005.</notes>
        <cve>CVE-2025-11226</cve>
        <cve>CVE-2024-12798</cve>
    </suppress>

    <!-- ─── Spring Web/WebMVC: CVE-2026-22740 ─────────────────────────
         Score: 6.5  WebFlux multipart temp files not deleted after request,
         allowing disk space exhaustion.
         Status: NO fix version available in 6.x branch as of this scan.
         Fix only exists in Spring 7.x (not yet adopted — major version jump).
         Mitigation applied in application code:
           1. multipart.max-file-size and multipart.max-request-size are set
              to conservative limits (10MB / 50MB) in application.yml.
           2. We do not use WebFlux reactive multipart in this project —
              only Spring MVC blocking multipart (not affected by this CVE).
         Review ticket: blockchain-sec-006. Reassess when Spring Boot 4.x
         (Spring Framework 7.x) is adopted. -->
    <suppress until="2026-12-31Z">
        <notes>CVE-2026-22740: WebFlux multipart temp file leak. No 6.x fix available.
            Project uses Spring MVC (blocking), not WebFlux reactive stack.
            CVE only affects WebFlux multipart. See blockchain-sec-006.</notes>
        <cve>CVE-2026-22740</cve>
    </suppress>

    <!-- ─── Spring Web/WebMVC: CVE-2026-22741 ─────────────────────────
         Score: 3.1  Cache poisoning in static resource chain when:
           (1) resource chain caching enabled AND
           (2) encoded resource resolution enabled AND
           (3) cache is empty at attack time.
         Status: NO fix version in 6.x branch as of scan.
         Mitigation: We do not use Spring's ResourceChainRegistration with
         EncodedResourceResolver + CachingResourceResolver in this project.
         Our static resources (example Spring Boot demo only) are served with
         the default resolver chain (no caching enabled in dev mode).
         Review ticket: blockchain-sec-007. Low priority due to 3.1 score
         and three required preconditions. -->
    <suppress until="2026-12-31Z">
        <notes>CVE-2026-22741: Static resource cache poisoning (score 3.1). No 6.x fix.
            Requires EncodedResourceResolver + CachingResourceResolver — not configured
            in this project. See blockchain-sec-007.</notes>
        <cve>CVE-2026-22741</cve>
    </suppress>

</suppressions>